gomodel:SYNGO_4569  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Authors used an antibody generated against rat SIPA1L2 to detect the protein in rat hippocampal cultures. Confocal and super-resolution imaging (STED) shows colocalization of the protein with the presynaptic markers Synaptophysin and Bassoon.. Experimental description: Immunostainings were performed in primary rat cultures. Generation of the antibody used in this study is described in [PMID: 17961154]: \"Full-length SPAR2 was cloned and sequenced after screening a k ZAPII (Stratagene, La Jolla, CA, USA) rat total brain cDNA library. (...) The first 93 amino acids of SPAR2 were expressed as glutathione-S- transferase (GST)-tagged fusion proteins in Escherichia coli BL21, purified, and used for generation of rabbit and guinea pig polyclonal antibodies. All antisera were affinity-purified using the appropriate recombinant fusion proteins.\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0575-6950" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1585-539X" ;
        dc:date           "2022-04-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4569" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

